Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Knidian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay medium pink-brown. Rectangular stamp with club symbol.
Type series: KT35 (Virginia Grace's unpublished K(nidian) T(ype) series)
Curator's comments: Names, Asklepiodoros, Agathodoros. Trimmed. Drawn by Petrie in his Journal, 1884-5, p.122, 28.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0298)
